# Service Patterns

Services contain business logic and orchestrate repository calls.

## Structure

```typescript
import repository from "./{feature}.repository";
import { Type1, Type2 } from "@/shared/types/{feature}.types";

class FeatureService {
  async methodName(param: Type1): Promise<Type2> {
    // Business logic here
    const result = await repository.findSomething();
    return this.mapToResponse(result);
  }

  private mapToResponse(data: DbModel): ApiResponse {
    // Data transformation
    return { ... };
  }
}

export default new FeatureService();
```

## Responsibilities

Services MUST:
- Contain business logic and validation
- Call repository methods for data access
- Transform database models to API response types
- Handle Date conversions (DB Date → ISO string)

Services MUST NOT:
- Access Prisma directly (use repository)
- Handle HTTP request/response
- Format error responses (throw errors instead)

## Data Mapping

```typescript
// ✅ Convert dates to ISO strings for API responses
private mapToResponse(entity: Entity): EntityResponse {
  return {
    ...entity,
    createdAt: entity.createdAt.toISOString(),
    updatedAt: entity.updatedAt.toISOString(),
    dateField: entity.dateField?.toISOString() ?? null,
  };
}
```

## Example

```typescript
class PersonService {
  async getPersonById(id: string): Promise<PersonResponse | null> {
    const person = await personRepository.findById(id);
    return person ? this.mapPersonToResponse(person) : null;
  }

  async createPerson(data: CreatePersonRequest): Promise<PersonResponse> {
    const person = await personRepository.create(data);
    return this.mapPersonToResponse(person);
  }

  private mapPersonToResponse(person: Person): PersonResponse {
    return {
      id: person.id,
      name: person.name,
      birthDate: person.birthDate.toISOString(),
      createdAt: person.createdAt.toISOString(),
      updatedAt: person.updatedAt.toISOString(),
    };
  }
}

export default new PersonService();
```
